  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Chop the<strong> baby plum tomatoes</strong> in half</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>fennel seeds</strong> to a <strong>pestle & mortar</strong> and grind (or chop if you don't have a pestle and mortar) to a fine powder</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/fiery-tomato-crab-fennel-linguine/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>halved tomatoes</strong>, <strong>chopped garlic</strong>,<strong> ground fennel seeds</strong> and <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!)</p><p>Cook for 3-4 min or until fragrant</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/fiery-tomato-crab-fennel-linguine/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, dissolve the <strong>vegetable stock mix </strong>in 150ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Stir through the <strong>tomato paste</strong> and 1 tsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tsp] </span><strong>sugar</strong> – this is your <strong>tomato stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/fiery-tomato-crab-fennel-linguine/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>linguine</strong> to a pot of plenty of <strong>boiled water </strong>with a large pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the<strong> </strong>linguine for 8-10 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the <strong>cooked</strong> <strong>linguine </strong>and return to the pot, reserving a cup of the<strong> starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/fiery-tomato-crab-fennel-linguine/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the tomatoes are fragrant, add the<strong> tomato stock</strong> and<strong> crab meat</strong> to the pan and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Season with a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until thickened to a pasta sauce-like consistency – this is your <strong>fiery tomato sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/fiery-tomato-crab-fennel-linguine/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel the <strong>Italian hard cheese</strong> until you end up with a pile of cheese shavings</p><p>Grate any <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>Italian hard cheese</strong></p><p>Chop the <strong>basil</strong> finely, including the stalks</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/fiery-tomato-crab-fennel-linguine/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>drained linguine</strong> to the fiery tomato sauce and gently stir together</p><p>Cook for 1 min further until the sauce begins to stick to the pasta – this is your<strong> fiery tomato, crab & fennel linguine</strong></p><p>Tip: Add a splash of starchy cooking water if your sauce is looking a little dry!</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/fiery-tomato-crab-fennel-linguine/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> fiery tomato, crab & fennel linguine</strong> topped with <strong>chopped basil</strong> and<strong> Italian hard cheese shavings</strong></p><p>Season with a grind of <strong>black pepper</strong> and drizzle with some <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
